"n. 愤怒，大怒 【英】 n.愤怒，大怒 (strong vengeful anger or indignation) 【例】 His wrath burst into flame.(他怒火喷发) n. (想复仇的)愤怒, 大怒 【记】wra = wry(v 扭曲), th死: 想wry死你, 是因为wrath. 源于: wreak(v 发泄怒火; 报仇) 【记】write + 音：撕，将写的东西撕掉→大怒 wrath (n.)  Old English wræððu ""anger,"" from wrað ""angry"" (see wroth) + -þu, from Proto-Germanic -itho (as in strength, width etc.; see -th (2))."
